{
  "texts": [
    "Conversely, another group of students may use AI tools more carefully as viewing them as supplementary purposes rather than primary sources of information (Stojanov et al., 2024; Koltovskaia et al., 2024).",
    "These students may tend to engage with AI in a more balanced manner by using the tool to verify their own solutions or to gain insights into complex problems (Koltovskaia et al., 2024).",
    "Moreover, some students might prefer not to use AI for learning purposes due to the concerns about its accuracy, reliability, and potential negative impacts on creativity (Haindl & Weinberger, 2024).",
    "Students' interaction with AI tools can also vary based on their prior knowledge and skills on the subject (Shoufan, 2023; Xia et al., 2023).",
    "Novice learners can use AI tools as a support system by helping them to overcome initial challenges in understanding basic concepts (Scholl and Kiesler, 2024; Xue et al., 2024)."
  ]
}